data.description: This is the perfect house for anyone who likes to live modestly yet elegantly, but with durable construction for the elements, children and/or pets. It is a perfect house for empty nesters, silver singles, or a retired couple.  Hardwood floors, large placed-on-diagonal tile, custom-made plantation shutters, crown molding, gorgeous light fixtures, and hard-wired surround sound is throughout. Top-grade custom Merillat kitchen cabinets with a lovely bay window in the kitchen nook opens to an inviting family room with a large, custom-built Chicago brick wood-burning fireplace with a gorgeous mantle.  French doors open to a spacious, screened lanai adorned with red brick pavers and a high split-level ceiling.  The large master suite boasts a his and hers closet with large garden tub and a separate, walk-in shower. There is a 2 1/2 car courtyard garage that complements a large yet quaint, brick paver front porch with plenty of room for a family sitting area. The house sits beautifully on a high crown above the road, and is one of the higher elevation lots in the neighborhood. Save money and enjoy the peace and quiet with foam insulation injected into the exterior walls, double-paned windows, and a radiant barrier installed in the roof. The entire A/C system was replaced end of 2017. This house has had just one elderly, single lady living in it for its entire 16 year history--she maintained it immaculately.  A new roof was added in 2019; while the old roof was still serviceable, the owner wished to ensure the house stayed in top condition.  So the new roof is upgraded to low-profile, dimensional shingle construction with premium underlayment and upgraded shingles designed to perform against 130 mph hurricane winds. New stainless-steel kitchen appliances were added in 2020.  The landscaping includes a color explosion variety of mature crepe myrtles, and magnolia trees, fragrant magnolias, and heat-tolerant, low-maintenance shrubs throughout.  The above average size lot for the area boasts plenty of room to add a pool in the backyard while still leaving enough room for the family and pets to spread out inside the premium white-vinyl privacy fence.
data.whatILove: The house boasts all the features of a much larger home, especially the master suite. It sits in a quiet, uncongested corner of Valrico, yet is less than five minutes away from major retail shopping, all types of restaurants, schools, gymnasiums, a library, and a fire station.
